ded by H3llBot-->\n| archivedate = 10 April 2008}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = National Council of Applied Economic Research\n| title = Traffic Survey of Mangalore and Malpe Ports: Report\n| publisher = Public Works Department, Government of Mysore\n| year = 1961\n| ref = 22}}\n* {{cite journal\n| last = Pinto\n| first = Pius Fidelis\n| authorlink = Pius Fidelis Pinto\n| year = 1999\n| title = History of Christians in coastal Karnataka, 1500\u20131763 A.D.\n| asin = B0000CPGW4\n| publisher = Samanvaya Prakashan\n}}.\n* {{cite book\n| last = Prabhu\n| first = Alan Machado\n| year = 1999\n| title = Sarasvati's Children: A History of the Mangalorean Christians\n| publisher = I.J.A. Publications\n| isbn = 978-81-86778-25-8\n| ref = harv\n}}.\n* \n* {{cite book\n| year = 1973\n| title = South Kanara District Gazetteer\n| series = Karnataka State Gazetteer\n| volume = 12\n| pages = 86\u2013125\n| chapter = People\n| publisher = Gazetteer Department ([[Government of Karnataka]])\n| ref = sc}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Riddick\n| first = John F.\n| title = The History of British India: A Chronology\n| url = https://books.google.com/?id=V2nGnWXV7coC&printsec=frontcover\n| year = 2006\n| access-date = 2 July 2008\n| publisher = Greenwood Publishing Group\n| isbn = 0-313-32280-5\n| ref = 23}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Shrihari\n| first = S.\n| title = Environmental Concerns for a Typical Fast Developing Indian City: Mangalore\n| year = 2007\n| publisher = Faculty of Civil Engineering, National Institute of Technology Karnataka, Surathkal\n| ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Somerset\n| first = Playne\n| author2 = Bond, E. W. |author3=Wright, Arnold |author4= Wright, Playne\n| year = 2004\n| title = Southern India: Its History, People, Commerce, and Industrial Resources\n| url = https://books.google.com/?id=8WNEcgMr11kC&printsec=frontcover\n| publisher = Asian Educational Services\n| isbn = 81-206-1344-9\n| access-date = 18 June 2008\n| ref = 24}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Thornton\n| first = Edward\n| title = The History of the British Empire in India\n| publisher = Cox and Wyman Printers\n| year = 1859\n| url = https://archive.org/details/historybritishe04thorgoog\n| access-date = 5 July 2008\n|isbn = 1331267595\n| ref = 27}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Townsend\n| first = George Henry\n| title = A Manual of Dates: A Dictionary of Reference to the Most Important Events in the History of Mankind to be Found in Authentic Records\n| publisher = Warne\n| year = 1867\n| url = https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_LtBCAAAAIAAJ\n| access-date = 19 August 2008\n|isbn = 0266609635\n| ref = 271}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book\n| last       = Bhat\n| first      = P. Gururaja\n| authorlink = P. Gururaja Bhat\n| title      = Antiquities of South Kanara\n| publisher  = Prabhakara Press\n| year       = 1969}}\n* {{cite book\n| last1      = Hoiberg\n| first1     = Dale\n| last2      = Ramchandani\n| first2     = Indu\n| title      = Students' Britannica India\n| url        = https://books.google.com/?id=kEj-2a7pmVMC&printsec=frontcover\n| access-date = 16 June 2008\n| year       = 2000\n| publisher  = Popular Prakashan\n| isbn       = 0-85229-760-2\n| chapter    = Mangalore\n| ref        = 10}}\n* {{cite book\n| last      = Venn\n| first     = T. W.\n| title     = Mangalore\n| year      = 1945\n| publisher = Wesley Press}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Mangalore}}\n{{Sister project links |b=no |commons=Mangalore |d=no |m=no |mw=no |n=no |q=no |s=no |v=no |voy=Mangalore |wikt=Mangalore}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20190315220959/http://www.dk.nic.in/ DC OFFICE, MANGALORE]\n* [https://www.webcitation.org/66HaSY8Zs?url=http://www.mangalorecity.gov.in/ Mangalore City Corporation Website]\n* [https://www.mangalorecity.com/ Mangalore City Website]\n* {{curlie|Regional/Asia/India/Karnataka/Localities/Mangalore/}}\n\n{{Localities in Mangalore}}\n{{Communities in Mangalore}}\n{{Portuguese overseas empire}}\n{{Karnataka topics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Mangalore| ]]\n[[Category:Former Portuguese colonies]]\n[[Category:Indian Ocean]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in India]]\n[[Category:Port cities in India]]\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Dakshina Kannada district]]\n[[Category:Cities in Karnataka]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses}}\n{{distinguish|Bangalore}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Mangalore\n| official_name                   = Mangaluru\n| settlement_type                 = [[City]]\n| total_type                      = [[City]]\n| image_blank_emblem              = Kodiyal Corporation logo.gif\n| blank_emblem_type               = Mangalore City Corporation\n| blank_emblem_size               = 100px\n| image_skyline                   = {{Photomontage\n| photo1a                         = Ivory Towers apartments at Falnir in Mangalore.jpg\n| photo2a                         = Turning Point Mall, Deralakatte, Mangalore.jpg\n| photo2b                         = Near the entrance of Corporation Bank head office in Mangalore.jpg\n| photo3a                         = Pilikula Botanical Garden in Mangalore - 10.jpg\n| photo3b                         = Mangalore infosys.jpg\n|spacing                          = 0\n|size                             = 240\n}}\n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = '''Left to right:''' [[Falnir]], [[Deralakatte]], [[Corporation Bank|Corporation Bank headquarters]], [[Pilikula Nisargadhama|Pilikula Botanical Garden]], [[Infosys|Infosys campus]]\n| image_seal                      = \n| nickname                        = Kudla (Tulu), Kodiyal (Konkani), Maikala (Beary)\n| map_alt                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Karnataka#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| pushpin_map_alt             