{"title_page": "Omotunde Adebowale David", "text_new": "{{short description|Nigerian radio presenter and actor}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{more citations needed|date=January 2019}}{{update|date=January 2019}}}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Omotunde Adebowale David\n| birth_name         = Omotunde Adebowale David\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| occupation         = [[Actress]], [[Radio presenter]]\n| children           = 4\n}}\n\n'''Omotunde Orepekan ''' is a [[Nigeria]]n radio presenter who hosts the radio programme, \u2018Oga Madam\u2019 on [[Wazobia FM 94.1]].\n\n== Early life ==\nOmotunde attended Ijebu-Ode Anglican Girls secondary school where she also spent part of her school days in a hostel.<ref name=tdl>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2016/10/29/lolo-1-i-have-three-sons-one-daughter-but-i-am-single/|title=Lolo 1: I Have Three Sons, One Daughter But I Am Single - THISDAYLIVE|date=2016-10-29|work=THISDAYLIVE|access-date=2018-11-03|language=en-US}}</ref> She is a graduate of Law from [[Lagos State University]] and she later went to law school.<ref name=tdl/>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n* City People Music Award for Female On Air Personality of the Year<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://buzznigeria.com/top-10-hottest-female-on-air-personalities-in-nigeria/|title=Top 10 Hottest Female On-Air-Personalities In Nigeria|date=2015-10-20|work=BuzzNigeria - Famous People, Celebrity Bios, Updates and Trendy News|access-date=2018-11-03|language=en-US}}</ref>\n* Nigerian Broadcasters Merit Award for Outstanding Radio Program Presenter- Lagos <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nbmawards.com/|title=Nigerian Broadcasters Merit Awards|last=Nbmawards.com|website=nbmawards.com|access-date=2018-11-03}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nShe is a single mother of three sons and a daughter.<ref name=tdl/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{improve categories|date=January 2019}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:David, Omotunde Adebowale}}\n[[Category:Livin